analysis_commentary: The number of cancelled elective operations fluctuates over time from quarter to quarter, with peaks in quarter 4 of nearly all the years that data have been collected. This is likely due to hospitals dealing with winter pressures. Overall, however, the trend shows that there has been a slight increase in the number of cancelled elective operations between quarter 1 of 1994/95 and quarter 1 of 2013/14.
